trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of message headers that are understood.
This class contains a collection of message headers that are understood.
SOAP processors at various layers (Security, Reliability, Transaction and application dispatcher) must add their MustUnderstand headers to this collection after processing the headers.
The dispatcher throws a `MessageHeader` fault if a header exists in the `Message.Headers` collection that must be understood, but is not found in this collection.
Adds the specified <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.MessageHeaderInfo> to this collection.
This implies that the specific header has been understood.
Contains additional information regarding a message header.
Verifies whether the specified <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.MessageHeaderInfo> is present in this collection.
Contains additional information regarding a message header.

Returns an enumerator that iterates through the collection.
An <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator> object that can be used to iterate through the collection.
Removes the specified <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.MessageHeaderInfo> from this collection.
